 and epistemologies in educational research. The contributors examine the roles and significance of ongoing transactions among connected social actors—students, peers, families, teachers—in a variety of institutional contexts. The book explores various uses and applications of relational sociology in education, while highlighting its promise to provide fresh insight into intractable problems of inequity in US schools.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aEducational sociologyzUnited States. 0aUniversities and collegesxResearchzUnited States. 0aUniversities and collegeszUnited StatesxSociological aspects. 4aEducation : Education. 4aEducation : Educational Research. 4aEducation : Higher Education. 4aEducation : Social Context of Education. 4aSociology : Sociology. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh1 aAntonio, Anthony Lising, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorr, Tamara Gilkes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerrare, Joseph J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFoster, Jesse, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKalamkarian, Hoori S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKolluri, Suneal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKolluri, Suneal, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLanford, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMccabe, Janice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPosselt, Julie R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTichavakunda, Antar A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTierney, William G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabula